The paper discusses capacity allocation in deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses commonly used architectures such as residual networks (cs.CV) and recurrent networks (cs.SY), which are subfields of computer vision and control systems, respectively. Additionally, the paper proposes scaling relations for weights and biases, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
